      "lesson title": "AI in Public Service Delivery: Reliability Risks",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "When public services rely on AI systems to make or support decisions, the consequences of those systems failing can be significant for the people who depend on them. This lesson introduces the key reliability risks that arise when AI is used in public sector contexts, from benefit assessments to healthcare triage and beyond. You will explore what can go wrong when automated systems produce errors, behave inconsistently, or are applied in situations they were not designed to handle. The lesson is aimed at those with little or no prior technical knowledge, and focuses on practical understanding rather than complex theory. By the end, you will have a clearer picture of why reliability matters so much when AI decisions directly affect citizens' lives and access to services.",
